B. Irresponsible Forwarding (IF)
The IF method handles the issue of flooding by introducing the ‚Äúforwarding probability‚Äù. The forwarding protocol of IF is shown in Fig. 2. After the inspection of TTL, the forwarding probability p is calculated based on the link distance of received packet. This is possible if every vehicle node knows its location by GPS and the location data is attached to the forwarded packet. The decision of forwarding or discarding the received packet follows the result of trial with success probability of p.
The p is calculated as;

