IV. CONCLUSION
A novel I2V multi-hop broadcast communication technique is proposed. The proposed Time-Controlled Broadcast Forwarding (TC-BF) method enables more efficient information delivery on the road compared to the existing broadcast packet forwarding methods such as flooding and Irresponsible Forwarding. PDR and forwarding efficiency of the proposed scheme are evaluated by using computer simulations. It is concluded that the proposed TC-BF can reduce unnecessary forwarding and achieve high PDR with extended communication range.
